channel.title: MS Paint - Electric Guitar - My project
channel.description:
Well I was very bored so I've tried to make two some-what different looking electric guitars.. Just one problem before I finish them what one do you think looks better? [IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar.png[/img]
[b]Well, I've decided to go with the second one.[/b] [b]UPDATE 1:[/b]
[ul][li]Added that little thing to the body of the guitar[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar1.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 2:[/b]
[ul][li]Added frets to neck of guitar[/li] [li]tuning pegs to headstock[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar2.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 3:[/b]
[ul][li]Shapened up the neck of the Guitar.[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar3.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 4:[/b]
[ul][li]Added nut near headstock[/li] [li]Fixed frets[/li] [li]Changed the look of tuning pegs on headstock[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar4.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 5:[/b] [size=7pt][b]on:[/b] June 01, 2008, 11:44:00 [/size]
[ul][li]Added pickups (still working on it)[/li] [li]added Bridge (still working on it).[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar5.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 6:[/b] [size=7pt][b]on:[/b] July 4, 2008, 01:23:27 PM [/size]
[ul][li]Fixed/Shapend up body of Guitar[/li] [li]Added Strap buttons[/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar6.png[/img] [b]UPDATE 7:[/b] [size=7pt][b]on:[/b] July 4, 2008, 02:19:50 PM [/size]
[ul][li]Changed the look of the bridge[/li] [li]Added Whammy Bar[/li] [li]Added Volume Controls[/li] [li]Added Pickup switch [/li][/ul]
[IMG]http://i180.photobucket.com/albums/x303/mystickid2k6/EletricGuitar7.png[/img]
